## Errors & Mistakes
- `timeout` is not on macOS (exit 127, "command not found: timeout"). Dropped it.
- `nvim --headless -c 'lua << \"LUA\" ... LUA'` failed: E5107 unexpected symbol
  near '<'. The :lua heredoc form does not work inside -c. Fix: write the script
  to /tmp/fm_diag.lua and run with -c 'luafile /tmp/fm_diag.lua' -c 'qa!', which
  also guarantees the user config (init.lua) is loaded first.

## Dead Ends
- Initial framing as a drop-in "replace" was wrong. filemention is an nvim-cmp
  completion source (type `@` in insert mode), NOT a telescope picker action.
  It has zero telescope integration. There is no analog for absolute paths,
  visual/normal-mode insertion, or relative-to-current-buffer. Surfaced this to
  the user, who chose to keep both.

## Hints for Future Agents
- filemention auto-registers as a cmp source via its plugin/filemention.lua shim
  (pcall require cmp -> cmp.register_source). No manual register needed; just add
  { name = "filemention" } to cmp.sources. setup() only applies config.
- The big gotcha: default filetypes are text-ish only (markdown/text/gitcommit/
  gitrebase/markdown.mdx/mdx/norg). In code buffers `@` is silently inert. We set
  filetypes = \"*\" to match the old picker's filetype-agnostic behavior. If `@`
  becomes noisy in code, narrow this to an explicit list.
- The telescope-insert-path removal+re-add nets to a ZERO diff vs HEAD; this
  commit's diff is purely the filemention additions. The two plugins are
  independent and both currently wired.

